data.name: Trapinch

attacks.name: Mini Earthquake
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: As it digs through the sand, its giant jaws crush any rocks that obstruct its path. It builds a funnel-shaped nest.

attacks.name: Pebble Throw
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Double Pinchers
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

data.name: Trapinch

attacks.name: Mountain Munch
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

data.flavorText: It lives in arid deserts. It makes a sloping pit trap in sand where it patiently awaits prey.

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Bind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Rock Smash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

data.name: Trapinch
data.flavorText: It makes an inescapable conical pit and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

attacks.name: Quick Bind
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Big Bite

abilities.name: Gather Sand
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Trapinch is your Active Pokémon, you may search your discard pile for a basic Fighting card and attach it to Trapinch.

data.flavorText: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

attacks.name: Sand Pit
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat until the end of your opponent's next turn.

data.name: Trapinch

attacks.name: Land's Pulse
attacks.text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 10 more damage.

data.flavorText: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.

data.name: Trapinch

attacks.name: Nest Building
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: Its jaws are strong enough to crush rocks but so heavy that it can't get up if it flips over. Sandile seize those moments as their chance.
